[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":248},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2020\u002F07\u002F23\u002Fclear-browser-hsts-https-localhost-redirect-fix\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2020\u002F07\u002F23\u002Fclear-browser-hsts-https-localhost-redirect-fix\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2020\u002F07\u002F23\u002Fclear-browser-hsts-https-localhost-redirect-fix\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2020\u002F07\u002F23\u002Fclear-browser-hsts-https-localhost-redirect-fix\u002F":223,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2020\u002F07\u002F23\u002Fclear-browser-hsts-https-localhost-redirect-fix\u002F":232},"\u002Fother\u002F20200723\u002F3866554212\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":202,"date":203,"description":204,"extension":205,"lang":206,"meta":207,"navigation":208,"path":209,"readingMinutes":210,"seo":211,"standalone":212,"stem":213,"tags":214,"tldr":220,"updated":220,"url":221,"__hash__":222},"content\u002Fen\u002FMisc\u002Fclear-browser-hsts-https-localhost-redirect-fix.md","Browser Forces Localhost to HTTPS? How to Clear HSTS in Chrome \u002F Edge \u002F Firefox","6655421238",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":189},"minimark",[11,16,29,33,36,51,57,64,74,84,90,98,106,110,113,118,125,131,137,140,146,150,160,164,175,179],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19,20,24,25,28],"p",{},"Web devs spend a lot of time on ",[21,22,23],"code",{},"localhost"," and ",[21,26,27],{},"127.0.0.1"," during dev. Sometimes the browser starts forcing you onto HTTPS, or you get errors like \"This site can't provide a secure connection\" \u002F \"localhost refused to connect\". Writing down the fix.",[12,30,32],{"id":31},"whats-happening","What's happening",[17,34,35],{},"Heads up — what's below isn't something I'd casually recommend trying just for fun. Use it when you've hit the actual problem.",[17,37,38,39,42,43,46,47,50],{},"Try entering ",[21,40,41],{},"https:\u002F\u002Flocalhost\u002F"," or ",[21,44,45],{},"https:\u002F\u002Flocalhost:8080"," in the address bar. You'll see errors like \"localhost refused to connect\", \"This site can't provide a secure connection\", or \"localhost sent an invalid response\", and the error code ",[21,48,49],{},"ERR_SSL_PROTOCOL_ERROR",". If you see this — congrats, you've reproduced the issue.",[17,52,53],{},[54,55],"img",{"alt":49,"src":56},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FH8aXd9W.png",[17,58,59,60,63],{},"If the error code is ",[21,61,62],{},"ERR_CONNECTION_REFUSED"," instead, that's just your server not being up — easy fix.",[17,65,66,67,69,70,73],{},"For ",[21,68,49],{},", dev tools like ",[21,71,72],{},"vue ui"," will refuse to load.",[17,75,76,77,42,80,83],{},"The \"This site can't provide a secure connection\" appears, and even after switching back to plain HTTP — like ",[21,78,79],{},"http:\u002F\u002Flocalhost\u002F",[21,81,82],{},"http:\u002F\u002Flocalhost:8080"," — you still land on the same error page.",[17,85,86],{},[54,87],{"alt":88,"src":89},"Can't provide secure connection","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-07-23%2014.08.31.png",[17,91,92,93,97],{},"This is because of HSTS — ",[94,95,96],"strong",{},"HTTP Strict Transport Security",".",[17,99,100,101,24,103,105],{},"In short — once a browser has seen HTTPS on a given origin, it remembers, and from then on it automatically upgrades any HTTP request to HTTPS. So ",[21,102,23],{},[21,104,27],{}," aren't immune — they can get cached the same way.",[12,107,109],{"id":108},"how-to-clear-it","How to clear it",[17,111,112],{},"A few browser-specific fixes.",[114,115,117],"h3",{"id":116},"google-chrome","Google Chrome",[17,119,120,121,124],{},"Open Chrome and go to ",[21,122,123],{},"chrome:\u002F\u002Fnet-internals\u002F#hsts",". Find \"Delete domain security policies\" and enter the domain you want to clear:",[17,126,127],{},[54,128],{"alt":129,"src":130},"Delete domain security policies","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-07-23%2014.28.27.png",[17,132,133,134,136],{},"After clicking \"Delete\" nothing visible happens — but try ",[21,135,79],{}," again and it works.",[17,138,139],{},"To check whether your browser has cached HSTS for a domain, use \"Query HSTS\u002FPKP domain\":",[17,141,142],{},[54,143],{"alt":144,"src":145},"Query HSTS","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-07-23%2014.29.21.png",[114,147,149],{"id":148},"microsoft-edge","Microsoft Edge",[17,151,152,153,155,156,159],{},"Edge uses the Chromium core, so the flow is the same. The URL changes — instead of ",[21,154,123],{},", type ",[21,157,158],{},"edge:\u002F\u002Fnet-internals\u002F#hsts",". The rest works identically, so I'll skip the screenshots.",[114,161,163],{"id":162},"firefox","Firefox",[17,165,166,167,174],{},"Firefox is simpler — just clear your browsing history. See ",[168,169,173],"a",{"href":170,"rel":171},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.thesslstore.com\u002Fblog\u002Fclear-hsts-settings-chrome-firefox\u002F",[172],"nofollow","this article"," for the detailed walkthrough.",[12,176,178],{"id":177},"references","References",[180,181,182],"ul",{},[183,184,185],"li",{},[168,186,188],{"href":170,"rel":187},[172],"Re-Hashed: How to clear HSTS settings in Chrome and Firefox",{"title":190,"searchDepth":191,"depth":191,"links":192},"",2,[193,194,195,201],{"id":14,"depth":191,"text":15},{"id":31,"depth":191,"text":32},{"id":108,"depth":191,"text":109,"children":196},[197,199,200],{"id":116,"depth":198,"text":117},3,{"id":148,"depth":198,"text":149},{"id":162,"depth":198,"text":163},{"id":177,"depth":191,"text":178},"Misc","2020-07-23 13:56:29","Web devs spend a lot of time on localhost and 127.0.0.1, but sometimes the browser forces HTTPS or throws \"This site can't provide a secure connection\" and \"localhost refused to connect\" errors. This post explains why — HSTS (HTTP Strict Transport Security) — and how to clear it in Chrome, Edge, and Firefox.","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002Fclear-browser-hsts-https-localhost-redirect-fix","2",{"title":6,"description":204},false,"en\u002FMisc\u002Fclear-browser-hsts-https-localhost-redirect-fix",[215,216,217,218,163,219],"Troubleshooting","Browser","Chrome","Edge","localhost connection refused",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2020\u002F07\u002F23\u002Fclear-browser-hsts-https-localhost-redirect-fix\u002F","I8bqEZgC7lUnshIC7r02yYiHFRc_pvL5xp6kE7L3BRY",{"newer":224,"older":228},{"url":225,"title":226,"date":227},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2020\u002F07\u002F26\u002Fjs-core-23-objects-variables-vs-object-properties\u002F","JavaScript Core Concepts (23) — Objects: Variables vs Object Properties","2020-07-26 15:35:31",{"url":229,"title":230,"date":231},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2020\u002F07\u002F21\u002Fpixijs-v5-24-animatedsprite\u002F","PixiJS V5 Tutorial (24) - Frame-by-Frame Animation with AnimatedSprite","2020-07-21 20:49:21",[233,238,243],{"url":234,"title":235,"date":236,"readingMinutes":237},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F06\u002F23\u002Fmac-stats-menu-bar-system-monitor\u002F","Stats — The Free Open-Source macOS Menu Bar System Monitor I Use Every Day (CPU, GPU, Temperature, Network)","2026-06-23 10:00:00","5",{"url":239,"title":240,"date":241,"readingMinutes":242},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F05\u002F26\u002Fhow-much-does-a-blog-really-earn-with-google-adsense\u002F","Can a Blog Really Make Tens of Thousands of Dollars a Month? Real Google AdSense Numbers, Explained","2026-05-26 21:00:00","6",{"url":244,"title":245,"date":246,"readingMinutes":247},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F05\u002F18\u002Fvscode-disable-integrated-browser-auto-open\u002F","VSCode Opens Every Link in the Integrated Browser? How to Disable Auto Takeover","2026-05-18 14:30:00","4",1784010281230]